    "short_description": "Trails, local shopping, craft beer, and farm-to-table dining on the western edge of the metro.",
    "long_description": "The Lenexa City Center area and adjacent Shawnee Mission Park offer one of the KC metro's most pleasant combinations of outdoor recreation and neighborhood dining. Start the day at Shawnee Mission Park, a sprawling Johnson County gem with miles of trails, a large lake, and a marina where you can rent kayaks, paddleboats, and fishing gear. \n\nAfter getting outside, the Lenexa City Center development just to the south is a walkable mixed-use district worth exploring. Lenexa Public Market is an excellent all-day food hall and gathering space, and the Made in KC Marketplace next door is the go-to spot for locally made goods, gifts, and a solid cup of coffee. \n\nFor a more upscale dinner, Silo Modern Farmhouse delivers a refined farm-to-table experience in a handsome setting just down the road.",
